    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-04T13:37:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-04T13:37:00-05:00" n="890"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d890">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/9–454: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 890<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Israel</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d890fn1">Sent also to Amman priority, Beirut, Baghdad,
                        Cairo, Damascus, Jidda, London, and Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-04T14:37:00-04:00"
                            >September 4, 1954—2:37 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>143. Acting Asst <gloss target="#t_Secy1">Secy</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_NEA1">NEA</gloss> advised Israel Chargé fourth as follows:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">Begin summary:</hi> Dept views with great concern
                            reports organized and armed force Israel military numbering several
                            hundred conducted operations Jordan territory area villages Beit Sira,
                            Beit Liqya and Khirbet al Misbah early morning Sept 2.</p>
                        <p>It is realized infiltrators from Jordan continue constitute serious
                            problem Israel, particularly to inhabitants agricultural settlements
                            close to <gloss target="#t_HKJ1">HKJ</gloss>-Israel armistice line. At
                            same time it must be said Israel’s apparent policy of organized and
                            armed retaliation has not only already been condemned but it has also
                            brought about heightened rather than reduced tensions along armistice
                            line.</p>
                        <p>It is to interest US as well as peoples of area that there be reduction
                            these tensions and, step-by-step move toward peace between Israel and
                            her neighbors. Peace in <gloss target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss> must be
                            painstakingly built through measures calculated diminish areas conflict
                            and lessen hatreds. Armed retaliatory raids not such measures.</p>
                        <p>Dept strongly hopes Israel will abandon armed retaliation, and that both
                            Israel and Jordan will cooperate wholeheartedly with appropriate <gloss
                                target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> organs in enforcement of General
                            Armistice Agreement. <hi rend="italic">End summary</hi>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Dept does not intend release foregoing to press but question from press at Sept 7
                    conference re reason for <persName corresp="#p_SR1">Shiloah</persName>’s call
                    will be answered if it arises along above lines. Tel Aviv may in its discretion
                    make similar statement to <gloss target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss>. Amman and other
                    addressees Arab states authorized informally advise Govts of action taken, if
                    deemed useful.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
